# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Editor / IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp

# Logs / temp
*.log
*.tmp

# Local secrets — never commit
*.env
.env*
*creds*

# Local backups
# Patterns here are prefix-tolerant on purpose: top-level folders carry sort prefixes
# (backups/ -> 00_backups/), and a bare name would silently stop matching after a rename.
*-backup.html
*backups/

# Test / tooling artifacts
.playwright-mcp/

# QA auto-loop (NB-46) generated run outputs — regenerated every run, never committed.
# (qa/last-report.txt IS tracked on purpose: the committed source-QA snapshot.)
qa/live-report.json
qa/triage-digest.md
qa/triage-out.json
qa/_i18n_uncovered.txt

# Owner-facing HTML deliverables — keep LOCAL, do not publish on the public Pages site
output/

# Local Claude tooling / context-mode (machine-specific)
.claude/

# Session pulse (NB-64) — rewritten by the Stop hook after EVERY turn, so tracking it would dirty
# the tree on every reply and bury real diffs. It is deliberately an INDEX into durable stores
# (the transcript + git), not a durable store itself: if the machine dies the pulse dies, but so
# does the transcript it points at, so tracking it would buy nothing. The tracked, machine-independent
# record stays docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md — the pulse's job is to make that file's ABSENCE loud.
docs/.session-pulse.md

# Recovery checkpoint (NB-64, re-architected 2026-07-16) — continuous machine state written by
# tools/recovery-checkpoint.ps1 on EVERY prompt/tool/stop/compact/session-end event. Same reasoning as
# the pulse above: it is a machine-local INDEX (session id, transcript path, git state, last owner
# message, error log), regenerated constantly, worthless once the machine dies. Tracking it would dirty
# the tree every turn AND risk sweeping the transcript path / owner message into a commit. Durable record
# stays docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md + docs/RESUME.md.
.recovery/

# wrangler local cache (tooling, not for repo)
.wrangler/
cloudflare/.wrangler/

# Agent audit output — regenerable, keep out of git. Publishing is already prevented by the
# deploy-pages.yml allowlist (it copies only explicitly named paths), so this is size hygiene only.
*auditbyagents/

# NOTE: the owner's strategy drafts (01_NikoLearn_Strategy_drafts/, *.docx) are deliberately
# TRACKED, not ignored — see 5b07582. They exist nowhere else, so git is their only backup, and
# the deploy allowlist means tracking them can never publish them. Do not re-add them here.

# design artifacts — keep local, do NOT deploy to Pages
*brand-preview/
niko-brand.html
node_modules/
www/
android/build/
android/app/build/
android/.gradle/
android/app/src/main/assets/public/
android/local.properties
*.apk
